doctype html
html(lang='en')
  head
    title MS service
    link(href='/bootstrap.min.js', rel='stylesheet', type='text/css')
  body
   div.container
    h1 API Timestamp Microservice
    h3 User stories:
    ol
     li I can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: May 1, 2017)
     li If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.
     li If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.
   
    h2 Example usage:
    p.
      #{url}#{unix} <br />
      #{url}#{natural} 
     
    h2 Example output:
    p { "unix": "#{unix}", "natural": "#{natural}" }
